<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") %>

<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <div class="profile-card p-4 p-md-5">
        <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="mv-icon-wrap m-0">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-code-fork"></i>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h1 class="fw-bold mb-0" style="font-size: 2rem; color: var(--nm-text);">Join Us & Contribute</h1>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Empower peer-to-peer education together</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-2" style="color: var(--nm-text); font-size: 1.4rem;">About Neuro_Mentor</h3>
        <p class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.75; font-size: 1rem;">
          Neuro_Mentor was born out of a real student struggle. The traditional course model forces students to buy entire subject bundles or skip difficult topics when studying late at night. Our platform provides a simple, direct solution: book peer mentors (like seniors) or industry professionals for just a few hours to clear doubts exactly when they arise.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4" style="border-color: var(--nm-border-light);">

        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3" style="color: var(--nm-text); font-size: 1.4rem;">How You Can Contribute</h3>
        <p class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.75; font-size: 1rem;">
          Neuro_Mentor is an open community project. Whether you are an engineering student, a software developer, or a UX designer, your contributions are welcome! You can help us improve the platform by:
        </p>
        
        <ul class="text-muted ps-3 d-flex flex-column gap-2 mb-4" style="line-height: 1.7;">
          <li>Adding new platform features (e.g. interactive calendar, mock exams, or chats).</li>
          <li>Refactoring backend API routes for better performance.</li>
          <li>Fixing bugs and writing automated test cases.</li>
          <li>Improving the UI responsiveness and user workflows.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="alert alert-dark p-4 border-0 d-flex flex-column flex-md-row align-items-md-center justify-content-between gap-3 mt-4" style="background: var(--nm-primary-xlight); border-radius: var(--nm-radius-lg);">
          <div style="flex: 1;">
            <h5 class="fw-bold mb-1" style="color: var(--nm-primary-dark); font-size: 1.1rem;">Contribute on GitHub</h5>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0" style="font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.5;">
              Submit pull requests, raise issues, or request feature additions on the official GitHub repository.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <a href="https://github.com/Ansh3721" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary rounded-pill px-4 py-2 text-nowrap" style="box-shadow: 0 4px 14px var(--nm-primary-glow);">
              <i class="fa-brands fa-github me-2"></i>GitHub Request
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-5 text-center">
          <a href="/" class="btn btn-light rounded-pill px-4 border">Back to Home</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
